contentrichtext.text: '''William Kelly''' or '''Bill Kelly''' may refer to: *[[Bill Kelly (American football)]] (1905–1931), American football player at the University of Montana and in the NFL *[[Bill Kelly (American football, born 1947)]], American football player and coach *[[Bill Kelly (outfielder)]], 19th-century American baseball player *[[Bill Kelly (first baseman)]] (1898–1990), American baseball player *[[Bill Kelly (politician)]], politician in Lapeer, Michigan *[[Bill Kelly (rugby league)]] (1892–1975), New Zealand rugby league footballer and coach *[[Bill Kelly (writer)]], American screenwriter *[[Kenneth Kelly]] (1905–1984), nicknamed "Bill", American football player and coach, head coach at Central Michigan University, 1951–1966 *[[William Kelly (artist)]], American artist *[[William Kelly (Bible scholar)]] (1821–1906), classicist and Biblical expositor *[[William Kelly (inventor)]] (1811–1888), American inventor of a steel smelting process *[[William Kelly (Labour politician)]] (1874–1944), British Labour politician *[[William Kelly (New York state senator)]] (1807–1872), New York politician *[[William Kelly (New Zealand politician)]] (1840–1907), New Zealand Member of Parliament *[[William Kelly (senator)]] (1786–1834), American Senator from Alabama *[[William McDonough Kelly]] (born 1925), political strategist and retired Canadian Senator *[[William Moore Kelly]] (1827–1888), businessman and politician in New Brunswick *[[William Osmund Kelly]] (1909–1974), mayor of Flint, Michigan *[[Willie Kelly (politician)]] (1877–1960), Australian politician ==See also== *[[William Kelley (disambiguation)]] {{hndis|name=Kelly, William}}
